A variety of process steps normally contribute to overall efficiency of evaluated industrial processes. In such a case, the PhO factors have to be combined to produce an overall factor that defines the process’s maximum optimization capability. The following equation couples a consumption process with a demand process (Keichel 2017):
3FPhOges=FPhOBFPhOV≥1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
