				\begin{document}$${F}_{{PhO}}^{{ges}}=\frac{{F}_{{PhO}}^{B}}{{F}_{{PhO}}^{V}}\ge 1$$\end{document}

VDI 4663 furnishes guidelines for evaluating the efficiency of transport processes, e.g., in heat exchangers. Keichel introduced the capacitive perspective for this purpose. It compares the energy that is transferred in real terms with the energy that could be transferred under physically optimal conditions, factoring in actual conditions, such as the device’s structural design (Keichel 2017).
4FPhOK=QrealQPhO≤1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
